text: Generated brief soil descriptions are created for major soil components.  The Urban land soil is a minor component.

The Catlin component makes up 99 percent of the map unit. Slopes are 2 to 5 percent. This component is on till plains on uplands. The parent material consists of loess over loamy till. Depth to a root restrictive layer is greater than 60 inches. The natural drainage class is moderately well drained.  Water movement in the most restrictive layer is moderately high.  Available water to a depth of 60 inches (or restricted depth) is high.  Shrink-swell potential is moderate. This soil is not flooded. It is not ponded. A seasonal zone of water saturation is at 32 inches during February, March, April. Organic matter content in the surface horizon is about 4 percent.  Nonirrigated land capability classification is 2e.  This soil does not meet hydric criteria.
